  locale="en"
>
  <section class="section">
    <h1>Levels of Play</h1>
    <p>
      Quadball programs across Canada welcome players at every stage. Explore the pathways below to
      find the right environment and learn how to get connected.
    </p>

    <article class="card">
      <h2>Youth</h2>
      <p>
        Introductory programming for ages 8 to 15 focuses on movement, teamwork, and inclusive play.
        Sessions are typically run through camps, community centres, and school partnerships.
      </p>
      <ul>
        <li>Look for youth specific postings on the <a href="/teams/">team directory</a>.</li>
        <li>Contact <a href="/contact/">Junior Development</a> to bring a clinic to your school or club.</li>
        <li>Access lesson plans, equipment lists, and safety briefs in the organizer toolkit.</li>
      </ul>
    </article>

    <article class="card">
      <h2>Recreational</h2>
      <p>
        Recreational leagues prioritize accessibility and social connection. These programs often run
        as mixed skill scrimmages or short seasonal leagues.
      </p>
      <ul>
        <li>Join a local club via the <a href="/teams/">Find a Team</a> page.</li>
        <li>Attend open practices or drop in sessions promoted on regional social channels.</li>
        <li>Volunteer as a coach or organizer to help new players learn the basics.</li>
      </ul>
    </article>

    <article class="card">
      <h2>Competitive</h2>
      <p>
        Competitive programs train for regional and national championships. Teams practice multiple
        times per week, travel for tournaments, and follow strength and conditioning plans.
      </p>
      <ul>
        <li>Review ranking events on the <a href="/events/">events calendar</a>.</li>
        <li>Connect with club leadership through their team listing to learn about tryouts.</li>
        <li>Officials and coaches can pursue certification through Quadball Canada clinics.</li>
      </ul>
    </article>

    <article class="card">
      <h2>National Team</h2>
      <p>
        The Team Canada program unites high performance athletes from coast to coast for
        international competition. Training pools are selected every two seasons.
      </p>
      <ul>
        <li>Watch for national team identification camps each fall.</li>
        <li>Ensure you are registered with a competitive club and in good standing with Quadball Canada.</li>
        <li>Reach out to <a href="/contact/">High Performance staff</a> for eligibility details and support.</li>
      </ul>
    </article>

    <section class="cta">
      <h2>Still unsure where to start?</h2>
      <p>
        Tell us about your goals and location and we will match you with the closest program or
        help you launch something new.
      </p>
      <a class="btn" href="/contact/">Connect with Quadball Canada</a>
    </section>
  </section>
</Layout>

